# Localization — Always Support AR & EN

Every screen built in this project must be fully localized in **both Arabic and English**.

## Required Steps for Every New String

1. **Add to `lib/l10n/intl_en.arb`** — English value
2. **Add to `lib/l10n/intl_ar.arb`** — Arabic value
3. **Add getter to `lib/generated/l10n.dart`** inside the `S` class
4. **Add to `lib/generated/intl/messages_en.dart`** — inside `_notInlinedMessages`
5. **Add to `lib/generated/intl/messages_ar.dart`** — inside `_notInlinedMessages`

## Usage in Widgets

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — always use S.of(context)
Text(S.of(context).logIn)

// ❌ BAD — never hardcode strings
Text('Log In')
```

## ARB Format

```json
{
  "myKey": "My Value",
  "@myKey": { "description": "Short description" }
}
```

## Generated Getter Format (`l10n.dart`)

```dart
String get myKey {
  return Intl.message('My Value', name: 'myKey', desc: 'Short description');
}
```

## Message Lookup Format (`messages_en.dart` / `messages_ar.dart`)

```dart
'myKey': MessageLookupByLibrary.simpleMessage('My Value'),
```

## Supported Locales

- `en` — English (LTR)
- `ar` — Arabic (RTL) — Flutter handles RTL layout automatically when `locale: Locale('ar')` is set
